  "title": "Engineer, Engineering",
  "description": "<p><strong>Responsibilities</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Review technical drawing by contractors to ensure that it adhere to industry compliance and contractor requirement.</li>\n  <li>Review Mechanical Design and Calculation to ensure compliance with relevant standards and office standards.</li>\n  <li>Check and ensure that the documentations comply with design.</li>\n  <li>Write, share and upload the design brief to Sharepoint.</li>\n  <li>Liaise with relevant parties to ensure required reports are updated and completed according to agreed timeline (eg. FAT report, SAT report, Progress report etc).</li>\n  <li>Review reports to ensure they meet the company and client’s requirements.</li>\n  <li>Coordinate Authority Submission for ongoing projects.</li>\n  <li>Coordinate and review with contractors and vendors for Technical Submissions (TS) based on the Employer’s Requirements or Technical Specifications.</li>\n  <li>Coordinate and review with the project team and consultants to ensure the Technical Submissions are in accordance to the specifications and requirements.</li>\n  <li>Compile and update the Equipment List, Procurement List and Asset List at different stages of the project.</li>\n  <li>Write, share and upload the Design Brief to Microsoft Sharepoint for respective projects.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><strong>Requirements</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Degree/Diploma in Electrical/Mechanical Engineering.</li>\n  <li>Proficient in Microsoft Office i.e. Microsoft Word, Excel and Powerpoint.</li>\n  <li>Experience in Microsoft Projects preferred.</li>\n  <li>Knowledge in project management tools, solutions, and techniques are highly desirable.</li>\n  <li>Good interpersonal, communication and people management skills.</li>\n  <li>Able to work in a fast-paced environment and meet tight deadlines.</li>\n  <li>Able to commit to long working hours and responsive to sudden client’s request.</li>\n  <li>A team player who works well with all internal and external teams involved in the project.</li>\n</ul>",
